1: AguilaTrades uses 20x leverage to go long on BTC, with a position value of $200 million;
2: Circle CEO: Stablecoins may be the most practical form of currency, and the "iPhone moment" has not yet arrived;
3: Coatue founder: Bitcoin volatility has decreased and will become a core asset in the investment portfolio;
4: The dormant 9.9-year Ethereum ICO whale address has been activated;
5: A certain address withdrew ZKJ and KOGE liquidity and then sold them in large amounts, which may cause the two currencies to fall by 3% in a short period of time;
6: Coinbase: Optimistic about the performance of the crypto market in the second half of the year, beware of the systemic risks of listed companies buying BTC with high leverage;
7: ConsenSys founder: LINEA will be the first to launch tokens, and multiple protocols will issue tokens;
8: Eastcom Peace will jointly explore the application of stablecoins with China Telecom Research Institute and TreeGraph Research Institute;
9: Echo Protocol's official X account was hacked, and the team said that the security of the protocol was not affected;
10: Spark: The first phase of the Ignition airdrop plan will be open for application soon.
